Can you remember how much you were paid then?

00:27:09.680 --> 00:27:12.680
£1.76 when I started.

00:27:12.680 --> 00:27:16.680
So were you given a pay rise every so often then?

00:27:16.680 --> 00:27:21.680
We usually got a pay rise every year, but because it was all age incremented.

00:27:21.680 --> 00:27:29.680
You know, if you started and you were 15, which I was 15, you had the wages of a 15-year-old.

00:27:29.680 --> 00:27:36.680
Then when you were 16 you'd have a bit more, and 17, and then you would get full pay at 18.

00:27:36.680 --> 00:27:39.680
You wouldn't get full pay until you were 18.

00:27:39.680 --> 00:27:42.680
But work in Peace Work, it didn't matter.

00:27:42.680 --> 00:27:45.680
But your rate was less though, wasn't it?

00:27:45.680 --> 00:27:51.680
Your basic rate was less, but you got the same money for the Peace Work.

00:27:51.680 --> 00:27:53.680
They didn't pay you less Peace Work.

00:27:53.680 --> 00:27:56.680
The rate for the Peace Work was universal.

00:27:56.680 --> 00:27:59.680
So you'd get what you earned.

